               <head>Grant; Hengrave, etc.; 1157-80</head>
               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p> HENGRAVE, &amp;c. Chirograph by which <persName>
                           <forename>Hugh</forename>, the abbot</persName>, 
                  and <orgName key="org_104015">convent of St. Edmund</orgName> grant and confirm to 
                  <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename>, <surname type="patronymic">son of Leo</surname></persName>, and
                  his heirs after him, the manor of <placeName type="manor" key="place_105036">Hengrave (Hemmegredhe)</placeName>; also the whole 
                  of the land which his father Leo held in <placeName key="place_105557">Westley (Westleia)</placeName> of
                  the hall of <placeName type="manor" key="place_105024">Fornham</placeName>, and land in <placeName key="place_104274">Cheventona</placeName> 
                  of the hall of <placeName type="manor" key="place_105013">Chevington (Cheventona)</placeName>, and land which he held in
                  <placeName key="place_105309">the Saxhams (Sexham)</placeName> of the hall of <placeName type="manor" key="place_105069">Great Saxham or Little Saxham (Sexham)</placeName>, &amp;c.; 
                  paying 110s. for <placeName key="place_105338">Hengrave (Hemmegredhe)</placeName>, 4s. at the hall of Fornaham for Westleia, 3s. at 
                  the hall of Cheventona for Cheventona, and 12d. at the hall of Sexham. 
                  (<origDate notBefore="1157" notAfter="1180">1157-80</origDate>.) 
                  [Printed in Gage's <title>Thingoe Hundred</title>, 1838, pp. 165-66.]
                  </p>
